New and Changed Standard Copilot Actions

Availability of copilot standard actions and related prompt templates can vary by edition and license.

Week of August 5, 2024
Draft or Revise Email
The Draft or Revise Email action can now chain more than one action together to handle multiple intents. For example, Einstein Copilot can help a user summarize a call and then email it to someone in a single request: “Summarize the latest call with this customer and email it to Sofia Rodriguez.”

Examples
“Summarize the Acme campaign and email it to John Smith.”
“Find the return policy for the Studio Pro headphones and email it to this customer.”
“Summarize the most recent Acme case and email it to Isaac Goldstein.”

Week of July 15, 2024
Summarize Record
When Einstein Copilot users request a summary of an account, now Einstein generates a more comprehensive and information-rich summary.

Get Forecast Guidance
The Get Forecast Guidance copilot action is now powered by a flow.

Week of July 8, 2024
Customize Work Summaries
Now, you can customize how Einstein drafts Work Summaries in Copilot.

Week of June 17, 2024
Draft a Gift Proposal
Nonprofit and Education Cloud customers can now use Copilot Actions Fundraising Gift Proposals to streamline writing compelling and personalized gift proposals.

Week of June 10, 2024
Send Meeting Request
Sales users can use the new Send Meeting Request copilot action to draft a meeting request to a recipient.

June ’24

Service Catalog Item (Reference Action Type)
Service Catalog customers can use the new Service Catalog Item reference action type to create custom actions from their Service Catalog items.
title: New and Changed Copilot Actions in Salesforce Summer '24
